author: @ARepublicIfYouCanKeepIt
text:
Something has always been wrong with Trump. Malignant narcissism, sociopathy, just plain arrogant and stupid. The list goes on. The fact is that Trump's only gotten worse over time. A condition that continues worsening.

Trump, as my father used to say, "was born on 3rd base, but is convinced he hit a triple." It's been proven that his daddy gave him the equivalent of over $400 million, yet Trump claims that he's self-made. It's also been proven that Trump holds the distinction of being the individual to have lost the most money in American history. Add to that that historians have ranked Trump as the worst President in our nation's history.

As much as I loathe Sen. Lindsey Graham, before he handed Trump his backbone, Graham got one thing right when he characterized Trump as "a race-baiting, xenophobic, religious bigot." Cruz, Rubio and others have likewise spoken truths about Trump, only to hand over their own spines in time. These people all had it right. They just lacked the moral courage to do what's right for the country; putting their political careers ahead of the nation.
